🏆 Jalen Hurts = NFC Offensive Player of the Week

Hurts passed for two touchdowns with no interceptions and had a career-high and franchise-record 157 rushing yards, the second-most rushing yards by a quarterback in a single game this season, in the Eagles’ Week 12 win over the Packers.

This is the first-career Offensive Player of the Week award for Hurts. He becomes the 10th Eagles quarterback to earn the honor and the first since Nick Foles (Week 16, 2018).

Hurts is the third former Crimson Tide quarterback to be named Offensive Player of the Week, joining Jeff Rutledge (Week 9, 1990) and Tua Tagovailoa (Week 2, 2022).

How much fun will Phillies fans have with Craig Kimbrel‼️

Phillies announce one-year deal with Kimbrel, a long time rival 

The #Phillies have signed right-hander #CraigKimbrel to a one-year contract, Phillies President of Baseball Operations David Dombrowski announced today.

Kimbrel, 34, ranks seventh on the all-time saves list with 394. He will enter 2023 with a chance to join the 400-save club that features only Mariano Rivera (652), Trevor Hoffman (601), Lee Smith (478), Francisco Rodríguez (437), John Franco (424) and Billy Wagner (422).

He signed a one-year deal with the Dodgers last offseason, posting a 3.75 ERA in 63 appearances with 72 strikeouts over 60 innings.

🚙 Moved to Motown Philly

I’ve become a main news anchor at CBS O&O in Detroit, where I will co-anchor the 5pm, 6pm & 11pm + streaming shows

📺 On-air with the big story starting tonight at 6pm & 11pm
📺 Made My TV News Anchor Debut last night at CBS in Detroit at 6pm

👊🏼 Thank you to everyone who has reached out the last few days, I can’t begin to tell you how much it means to me!

It’s been a very emotional time for me & my family, to leave home & now make a new one, as I leave the sports chair & move to the anchor chair. 

I can’t help but think how far I’ve come from interviewing Phillies & NBA stars for my High School TV station at Bensalem in the ‘90s, wanting to be just like Gary Papa. 

To hold that mic, and to sit on that desk years later, was a dream come true.

Reading the thousands of messages on Facebook from loyal viewers, who welcomed me into their homes for 13 years, reminded me just how special you are! 

It’s a Philly Thing!

With Brotherly 💙 Love, 
✌🏼 Jeff Skversky

Nick Sirianni on Crying Before the Super Bowl

“I’ve dreamed about this since I’ve been two years old. I said to our guys, ‘some of you guys have been dreaming about this since you’ve been two, some of you since you’ve been in peewee football, some of you since high school, college or even when you got to the pros. But we’ve all been dreaming of it.’ You know, growing up in a family with a dad that’s a football coach, older brothers that play football, this is what you dream of being in this moment. It’s just emotional because there’s a lot of work, not just by myself, but a lot of people. Starting with my wife and my kids, my brothers, my dad and just so many people – coaches that I’ve had, teammates that I’ve had that helped me get to this moment. So it’s just emotional in that moment knowing where we were at that moment.”
